                        <h3 class="mt-3 mt-md-0">Sayyid Abdurahman Unni Koya Thangal <span>(1941 -2018 )</span></h3>
                        <p>Founding President</p>
                        <p>Sayyid Abdurahman Unni Koya Thangal was the founding President of Darul Irfan Islamic
                            Academy. Born in 1941 to a Sayyid family in a rural area, later settled in Thambanagadi- the
                            nearest town to Pandikkad. Years of Dars education in the Masjids of Thuvvur, Mudikkode,
                            Vettathur, and Pullara made him a religious scholar and planted seeds of social service for
                            the Muslim League. Being a Sayyid, ‘Alim, and a public speaker at the same time, he started
                            his political life in 1968 as Pandikkad Panchayath Muslim League president and continued in
                            that designation for five decades until his last breath. He also decorated the designations
                            of Mulsim League State Counsilor, Muslim League Wandoor Constituency president, and Muslim
                            League Manjeri Constituency treasurer. Alongside he presided over Himayathu ‘Aqaidi Sunniyya
                            and Darul Irfan Islamic Academy. <br><br>
                            Like Panakkad Kopdappanakkal House, Pandikkad Thangalpadi House’s doors were open all day
                            and night for social resolutions and problem-solving. He put a keen interest in educational
                            reformation and thus he supervised building institutions such as Darul Irfan Islamic
                            Academy, Al-Farooque Orphanage, Al-Farooque Shareeath College Oravampuram, and Al-Farooque
                            English Medium Higher Secondary School.</p>
