                <h3>O.T. MOOSA MUSLIYAR <span>(1946 - 2021)</span></h3>
                <p>Founding General Secretary</p>
                <p>O.T. Moosa Musliyar, a member of Samastha Mushavara, was the founding secretary of Darul Irfan
                    Islamic Academy. Born in 1946 to Ottakath Mammutty Musliyar and Fatima. Starting from Vakkethodi
                    Muhammed Muliyar’s Pallikoodam, his primary education was at Kadambode G.M.L.P School. His religious
                    studies started in K.C Jamaludheen Muslaiyar’s Dars and progressed in Jamia Nooriyya Arabiyya as he
                    graduated with the certificate of Faizy. Being ‘Alim of the then Kerala, he started teaching in the
                    Dars system in many regions of the state such as Mudikkode Kuttasheri, Eriyad, Valluvambram, and
                    Khaja Nagar. Later, he lived for some years in Saudi Arabia. With his profound mastery and restless
                    educational services, he was an honored member of Samastha Kerala Jamiyyathul Ulama Muhavara, a
                    40-’Alims’central Sunni-Shafi'i Muslim scholarly body in Kerala established in 1926. Alongside he
                    was Qadhi, a member of Samastha Malappuram District Mushavara, President of Samastha Eranad Thaluk,
                    and Secretary of Himayathu ‘Aqaidi Sunniyya. <br><br>
                    O.T. Usthad played a vital role in the establishment of Darul Irfan Islamic Academy even before 2014
                    as he suggested O.T Ummer Master, a familymate, donate land for Darul Irfan realizing the
                    opportunity of a great Sunni Islamic institution in the Pandikkad area. He, Sayyid Unnikoya Thangal,
                    and PMH Bappu Haji collectively carried out the leading role of building an institution, home to
                    300+ students and 25 staff. His demise was on 9th February 2021 at his residence in Mudikkode. His
                    body was laid to rest at the Mudikkode Juma Masjid.
                </p>
